+// HMR patch: registration cloud keep-alive count. NDT_OMP/GICP hold pointers
+// into their input source/target clouds, so we retain the last N clouds to avoid
+// a use-after-free (including the shutdown-leak path). Upstream pinned this at
+// 4096 (retain ~everything), which is large, ever-growing RAM; 4 cuts memory
+// markedly with no accuracy cost -- these deques are write-only lifetime buffers,
+// never read back into registration (alignment always uses only the latest
+// cloud). 2 is the theoretical floor (current + previous); 4 keeps a margin.
+constexpr std::size_t kRegistrationSourceCloudKeepAliveCount = 4;
+constexpr std::size_t kRegistrationTargetCloudKeepAliveCount = 4;
 
